<TITLE> Jayasuriya joins Lancashire as cover for Muralitharan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, June 13 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Sanath Jayasuriya, one of the world's most devastating one-day players, is to join Lancashire on a short-term contract to cover for the absence of fellow Sri Lankan Muttiah Muralitharan. A statement from the English county on Wednesday said all-rounder Jayasuriya, 37, who retired from international cricket after this year's World Cup, would replace Muralitharan from June 19-July 20 while the off-spinner plays in Sri Lanka's test series against Bangladesh. Lancashire cricket manager Mike Watkinson said: "Sanath and Twenty20 Cricket is an exciting prospect. He has a tremendous record in one-day cricket and we are delighted he will be joining us
